(
<figureCitation box="[551,678,1905,1931]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-13" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,183,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-77@1.[170,1417,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-13. Plumosa nigrimaculata n. sp. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Tip of abdomen, left lateral view. 4. Style. 5. Aedeagus, caudal view. 6. Aedeagus, lateral view. 7. Connective. 8. Abdominal apodemes. 9. Forewing. 10. Hindwing. 11. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 12. Subgenital plate, inner-lateral view; P. emarginata Sohi, 1977: 13. Aedeagus, lateral view (after Sohi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133704/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Figs. 1–13</figureCitation>
