</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1435,1975,2033]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,972]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,301,1975,1999]" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Morphology:</emphasis>
Structural characters as in the genus description. Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[940,1005,1975,1998]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-13" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,183,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-77@1.[170,1417,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-13. Plumosa nigrimaculata n. sp. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Tip of abdomen, left lateral view. 4. Style. 5. Aedeagus, caudal view. 6. Aedeagus, lateral view. 7. Connective. 8. Abdominal apodemes. 9. Forewing. 10. Hindwing. 11. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 12. Subgenital plate, inner-lateral view; P. emarginata Sohi, 1977: 13. Aedeagus, lateral view (after Sohi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133704/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) testaceous, with large blackish-brown patch at anterior margin and pair of small faint ovoid dots. Eyes black. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1025,1087,2010,2033]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-13" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,183,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-77@1.[170,1417,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-13. Plumosa nigrimaculata n. sp. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Tip of abdomen, left lateral view. 4. Style. 5. Aedeagus, caudal view. 6. Aedeagus, lateral view. 7. Connective. 8. Abdominal apodemes. 9. Forewing. 10. Hindwing. 11. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 12. Subgenital plate, inner-lateral view; P. emarginata Sohi, 1977: 13. Aedeagus, lateral view (after Sohi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133704/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) broad, with obvious impressed pattern in the middle area, nearly diamond shaped; testaceous near anterior margin, middle area and posterior margin dark brown; scutellum testaceous, triangular, with black apex. Face (
<figureCitation box="[904,970,186,209]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-13" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,183,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-77@1.[170,1417,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-13. Plumosa nigrimaculata n. sp. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Tip of abdomen, left lateral view. 4. Style. 5. Aedeagus, caudal view. 6. Aedeagus, lateral view. 7. Connective. 8. Abdominal apodemes. 9. Forewing. 10. Hindwing. 11. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 12. Subgenital plate, inner-lateral view; P. emarginata Sohi, 1977: 13. Aedeagus, lateral view (after Sohi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133704/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) light brown. Frontoclypeal area blackishbrown, with several dark brown transverse streaks on each side; most part of anteclypeus brownish-black. Forewing (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1-13" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,183,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-77@1.[170,1417,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-13. Plumosa nigrimaculata n. sp. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Tip of abdomen, left lateral view. 4. Style. 5. Aedeagus, caudal view. 6. Aedeagus, lateral view. 7. Connective. 8. Abdominal apodemes. 9. Forewing. 10. Hindwing. 11. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 12. Subgenital plate, inner-lateral view; P. emarginata Sohi, 1977: 13. Aedeagus, lateral view (after Sohi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133704/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) semitransparent, light brown, without markings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
