<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,972]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,371,290,314]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Male genitalia:</emphasis>
Abdominal apodemes short and thick, extending to 3rd segment (
<figureCitation box="[1093,1160,290,313]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-13" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,183,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-77@1.[170,1417,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-13. Plumosa nigrimaculata n. sp. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Tip of abdomen, left lateral view. 4. Style. 5. Aedeagus, caudal view. 6. Aedeagus, lateral view. 7. Connective. 8. Abdominal apodemes. 9. Forewing. 10. Hindwing. 11. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 12. Subgenital plate, inner-lateral view; P. emarginata Sohi, 1977: 13. Aedeagus, lateral view (after Sohi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133704/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of 8th segment with long fine white setae (
<figureCitation box="[537,601,325,348]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-13" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,183,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-77@1.[170,1417,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-13. Plumosa nigrimaculata n. sp. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Tip of abdomen, left lateral view. 4. Style. 5. Aedeagus, caudal view. 6. Aedeagus, lateral view. 7. Connective. 8. Abdominal apodemes. 9. Forewing. 10. Hindwing. 11. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 12. Subgenital plate, inner-lateral view; P. emarginata Sohi, 1977: 13. Aedeagus, lateral view (after Sohi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133704/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[721,784,325,348]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-13" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,183,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-77@1.[170,1417,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-13. Plumosa nigrimaculata n. sp. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Tip of abdomen, left lateral view. 4. Style. 5. Aedeagus, caudal view. 6. Aedeagus, lateral view. 7. Connective. 8. Abdominal apodemes. 9. Forewing. 10. Hindwing. 11. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 12. Subgenital plate, inner-lateral view; P. emarginata Sohi, 1977: 13. Aedeagus, lateral view (after Sohi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133704/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) very broad, dark brown, with numerous long white setae on lateral surface and also with group of long fine setae at the base of pygofer close to ventral margin. Pygofer lobe (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1-13" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,183,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-77@1.[170,1417,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-13. Plumosa nigrimaculata n. sp. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Tip of abdomen, left lateral view. 4. Style. 5. Aedeagus, caudal view. 6. Aedeagus, lateral view. 7. Connective. 8. Abdominal apodemes. 9. Forewing. 10. Hindwing. 11. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 12. Subgenital plate, inner-lateral view; P. emarginata Sohi, 1977: 13. Aedeagus, lateral view (after Sohi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133704/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
), with dorsal appendage long and wide, curved down apically, area near base of dorsal appendage with two transverse bands. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[415,530,429,452]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-13" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,183,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-77@1.[170,1417,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-13. Plumosa nigrimaculata n. sp. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Tip of abdomen, left lateral view. 4. Style. 5. Aedeagus, caudal view. 6. Aedeagus, lateral view. 7. Connective. 8. Abdominal apodemes. 9. Forewing. 10. Hindwing. 11. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 12. Subgenital plate, inner-lateral view; P. emarginata Sohi, 1977: 13. Aedeagus, lateral view (after Sohi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133704/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Figs. 3, 12</figureCitation>
) brownish, with lamelliform process on inner lateral surface near apex, with numerous short microsetae basally along upper lateral margin and several long white fine setae at apex. Style (
<figureCitation box="[1264,1328,464,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-13" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,183,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-77@1.[170,1417,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-13. Plumosa nigrimaculata n. sp. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Tip of abdomen, left lateral view. 4. Style. 5. Aedeagus, caudal view. 6. Aedeagus, lateral view. 7. Connective. 8. Abdominal apodemes. 9. Forewing. 10. Hindwing. 11. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 12. Subgenital plate, inner-lateral view; P. emarginata Sohi, 1977: 13. Aedeagus, lateral view (after Sohi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133704/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) long and slender, with 3 small teeth apically. Aedeagal shaft in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[859,922,498,521]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-13" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,183,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-77@1.[170,1417,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-13. Plumosa nigrimaculata n. sp. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Tip of abdomen, left lateral view. 4. Style. 5. Aedeagus, caudal view. 6. Aedeagus, lateral view. 7. Connective. 8. Abdominal apodemes. 9. Forewing. 10. Hindwing. 11. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 12. Subgenital plate, inner-lateral view; P. emarginata Sohi, 1977: 13. Aedeagus, lateral view (after Sohi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133704/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) wide, nearly L-shaped, produced in long dorsal distal lobe, with short thin tooth on dorsal margin and pair of small ventral processes basally. Gonopore (
<figureCitation box="[1295,1360,533,556]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-13" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,183,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-77@1.[170,1417,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1-13. Plumosa nigrimaculata n. sp. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view. 2. Face. 3. Tip of abdomen, left lateral view. 4. Style. 5. Aedeagus, caudal view. 6. Aedeagus, lateral view. 7. Connective. 8. Abdominal apodemes. 9. Forewing. 10. Hindwing. 11. Pygofer lobe, lateral view. 12. Subgenital plate, inner-lateral view; P. emarginata Sohi, 1977: 13. Aedeagus, lateral view (after Sohi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133704/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) large, ventral, apical. Connective broad, lamelliform, nearly Y-shaped, with a short broad central lobe between two arms.
</paragraph>
